headlines.description: — Danny Green scored 21 points, Cedi Osman added 19 and the Cleveland Cavaliers beat the Orlando Magic 118-94 on Thursday night in a game in which both teams rested their starters.
headlines.shortLinkText: Green, Osman lead Cavaliers to 118-94 win over Magic

headlines.description: — Jimmy Butler and Tyler Herro each scored 24 points and the Miami Heat kept alive their hopes of avoiding the NBA's play-in tournament with a 129-101 victory over the Philadelphia 76ers on Thursday night.
headlines.shortLinkText: Jimmy Butler, Tyler Herro help Heat rout 76ers 129-101

events.name: Portland Trail Blazers at San Antonio Spurs

headlines.description: — Keita Bates-Diop had 25 points, Julian Champagnie and Keldon Johnson added 24 points each and the San Antonio Spurs beat the short-handed Portland Trail Blazers 129-127 on Thursday night in the first NBA game in Texas’ capital city.
headlines.shortLinkText: Bates-Diop leads Spurs past Blazers in inaugural Austin game

events.name: Oklahoma City Thunder at Utah Jazz

headlines.description: — Shai Gilgeous-Alexander scored 22 points and the Oklahoma City strengthened their hopes of reaching the play-in tournament with a 114-98 victory over the short-handed Utah Jazz on Thursday night.
headlines.shortLinkText: Thunder beat Jazz 114-98, strengthen play-in hopes

headlines.description: — Chris Paul made a career-high seven 3-pointers and the Phoenix Suns won their season-best seventh game in a row, holding off the short-handed Denver Nuggets 119-115 on Thursday night.
headlines.shortLinkText: Paul makes 7 3s, Suns beat Nuggets for 7th straight win
